## 14. RISKS & MITIGATIONS

| Risk | Impact | Mitigation |
|---|---|---|
| No live match during review (July 19–29) | High | F8 deterministic replay with real recorded data |
| Live TxLINE stream empty | High | Recorder always on; replay fallback |
| MM seen as "given idea" (novelty score) | Medium | Emphasize event-aware self-hedging + verifiable receipts |
| Perceived as agent-controlled entry | Medium | Human-authored docs + clean commit history |
| Over-scoping kills MVP | High | Strict P0/P1/P2 discipline; 3 markets, 1 match |
| Fake-looking metrics in demo | High | All numbers from real replay output, never pre-picked |

---

## 15. FINAL PITCH

> "Most market makers earn until the match changes. RAVEN is built for the moment it does. It prices live football markets using TxLINE consensus odds, earns spread under normal flow, withdraws from toxic event windows the instant a red card or penalty is cryptographically verified, neutralizes exposure across connected markets, and proves every quote, hedge and risk decision on Solana. We don't predict the match. We survive it — profitably, and verifiably."

